Commission member Delfin Lazaro estimated that 70 officers involved in last December's coup attempt, which came closest to toppling Aquino, are still at large and still plotting. He expected another standoff and hoped for other camps to defect. Most ended in embarrassing standoffs or dragged on for days, as top military leaders hedged on ordering troops to fire on other soldiers. Only in the Philippines. And despite widespread fears that the Oct 4-6 uprising would quickly spread to military garrisons on other islands and become a major threat to Aquino, leaders of the rightist military underground failed to move. 